defaultQ6. Do you agree with the proposal that legal aid should be removed for all cases assessed as having “borderline” prospects of success?
default&#xa0;
defaultThis proposal would represent a further ‘chilling’ effect for the testing of legal disputes where the issue may be of fundamental importance and relate to a new or undetermined decision or policy, but where the resolution of the claim would be a developmen
defaultt of the law and so cannot be reliably guided by previous cases to establish a likelihood of success. 
defaultThere is insufficient basis for a need to remove funding from borderline cases irrespective of the public importance of the issues at stake
default, or the indivi
defaultdual’s own interest in the claim
default (which may be very substantial even if not
default a case of the limited types 
defaultexcepted from the prospects of success criteria)
default.
default I do not agree with the proposal.
