defaultQ31. Do you agree with the proposal that fees for self-employed bar
defaultristers appearing in civil (non-family) proceedings in the County Court and High Court should be harmonised with those for other advocates appearing in those courts.
default&#xa0;
defaultThis 
defaultproposal does not recognise the use of counsel in specialist work where counsel is c
defaultheaper because of the specialist background knowledge allowing less time to be spent on the case, and does not make any reasonable comparison of like situations. 
defaultFor example in judicial review work 
defaultin the main, and almost universally if not universally in 
defaultcomplicated or specialist areas of judicial review work the 
defaultadvocacy and key drafting is done by Counsel. 
defaultHigh Court work 
defaultrequires higher rights of audience that the majority of solicitors in civil work do not 
defaulteven 
defaultpossess. 
defaultThe payment structure is not an 
defaultanomaly, but a representation of the relationship to private rates to the legal aid rates, where if the disparity is too great
default the best barristers will simply not be prepared to undertake publicly-funded work.
default That will create a two-tier quality system ana
defaultthema to a true justice system. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe reduction proposed 
defaultwould also 
defaultreinforce the problems facing judicial review work 
defaultwhere barristers would not be 
defaultable to rely even on current rates of recompense to subsidise cases where permission was not granted. 
defaultThe potential for “enhancement” of fees 
defaultis particularly inappropriate to judicial review work. It is unlikely to be possible to establish a claim is “exceptional” 
default(Annex I) 
defaultor 
defaultwas conducted in an “exceptional” manner, where the court will 
defaultsimply 
defaultnormally e
defaultxpect to see barristers appearing and conducting such cases with that same speed, efficiency
default, skill and expertise, and will expect most judicial review cases to be of complexity
default, albeit the complexity and skill in a judicial review claim may 
defaultordinarily be 
defaultthought of as being exceptional in the large majority of such cases
default.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultIn judicial review work at least there is no justification for reducing the fees paid to barristers, as there is no ‘anomaly’ because the type of work that requires judicial review is 
defaultsimply not appropriate to be conducted by a solicitor, as present practice already evidences.
default It will further be unduly difficult to establish one skilfully-presented judicial review is exceptional compared to other skilfully-presented judicial reviews.
default&#xa0;
defaultI sincerely hope that the Ministry of Justice will revisit the proposals in light of the responses to the consultation, including this one, and alter the proposals before significant damage is done to the legal profession and to the 
defaultpublic confidence and f
defaultaith in the justice system and fairness of British society.
